Finally, add half of her age when she was 2 years old to her current age. This is because you mentioned that your sister was "half my age" when she was only two years old. So, let's call this HALF_AGE_AT_2. Now we can calculate the total number of years between now and then by doing:
CURRENT_AGE + 1/2 * CURRENT_AGE = TOTAL_YEARS (TOTAL_YEARS = Current Age + Half Her Age at Time She was 6 Years Old). So, let's plug in the numbers we have.
Current Age = 80 years old
CURRENT_AGE = 80;
Her Age at time she was 6 Years Old = CURRENT_AGE - 6;
HALF_AGE_AT_2 = (CURRENT_AGE / 2);
TOTAL_YEARS = Current Age + Half Her Age at Time She was 6 Years Old) + HALF_AGE_AT_2);
